name: Hulkencarne Sorcerer (pre-supported)
description:
Fleshbound sorcerers are blood-scholars, commanding not only warp energies but blood itself - ripping it from living bodies, crushing organs within and drawing crimson streams through the air like living weapons. The Hulkencarne Sorcerer walks the battlefields within the Hulkencarne war suit, a heavier and more armoured version of the standard Exocarne. Draped in an unholy intestinal cloak and curse tusks, this Fleshbound Lord is one of the most feared of all the Kav'Zul demons.

This set features a poor Dredgemarine lying lifeless on the base, his blood drawn from the cracks in his defeated armour and spiraling into piercing darts. There is also be a non-blooded dredge marine, allowing you to use him as a fallen brother in your dredge armies. The Hulkencarne Sorcerer is a multipart set that is completely compatible with the Hulkencaren Guard - a full squad of multipart heavy Fleshbound elites. All arms, torso, legs and head are interchangeable.

Assembly advice: The head has a tab on it so that it slots in place, with the torso. If you wish to repose the head you can simply cut off the tab.

This set comes with a 40mm base with magnet slots (7mm x 3mm).

Folder includes both supported and unsupported parts, as well as the LYS file, in case you need to adjust your supports.

Digital download. No physical product will be shipped to you.

Disclaimer: This product is an original design by Mezgike Pty Ltd, created for hobby, display, and non-commercial tabletop use. All Mezgike miniatures exist within the original Mezgike universe and are not affiliated with, endorsed by, or associated with any other brand, company, or game system. References to “proxy miniatures” or “compatible scales” are descriptive only and do not imply any association or endorsement by other creators or companies.

name: Obsidian Guard - Immortals - Blademaster
description:
This modular character builder is cross compatible with the Obsidian Guard Eternals kit.

Faction Lore: In the age of war, on old earth, the Obsidian Guard stand as one of the last vestiges of the age of enlightenment. Once their armies were known as the Solar Guardians and had within their care the welfare of the entirety of the Sol system. Now diminished, they still stand above the petty squabbles of the techno barbarians that vie for land upon the ashen heap of terra. They endure to protect what remains from world - ending caticlysm, and from threats that come from beyond the light of Sol. Only a fool would try and dislodge them from their mountain fortresses, for no force on earth is so well equipped or so trained in the use of lost technology.

Even among the legions of the Obsidian Guard, the immortals stand above. The Gene-sorcery and technology used in their creation has been lost for thousands of years, and yet their numbers have not substantially lessened. They are the paragons of a brighter age, and the living memory of humanity. Theirs alone to wield are the weapons and tools of a species that conquered a galaxy, learned the means to forge new stars and perfect worlds from the detritus of the universe.

Every part is included with both supported and non-supported versions for ease of printing. Test models were made on an phrozen sonic mini. Printed at 0.05mm layer height, Elegoo's ABS 3.0 resin (Red Clay) 1.0s standard exposure. Models are scaled for 30mm gaming. Parts require support. Recommended resin printing.

name: Exalted Scion - Scout Bikes
description:
Exalted Scion - Scout Bikes

This fully modular kit comes with all you need to build a scout bike squad with multiple weapon options. 

Faction Lore The Fabricarii Houses: The Noble houses fabricar are, perhaps, the most technologically advanced society on terra. Many are their illustrious halls of devices, radiant in ancient gold and marble. In war only a very few organic beings are ever seen, the majority of their hosts seeming to be living statues, or great engines emitting deadly light. In truth the Fabricarii are a decadent society in decline, their numbers ever dwindling, and their self importance preventing them from seeing even their greatest flaws.

House primus maintaind the military arm of the fabricarii alliance. Arrayed in splendor their troops march to war each one wearing bespoke relics of a glorious marshal legacy.

Every part is included with both supported and non-supported versions for ease of printing.Test models were made on an anycubic photon. Printed at 0.025mm layer height, Elegoo's ABS 3.0 (Red Clay) 1.0s standard exposure. Models are scaled for 30mm gaming. Parts require support. Recommended resin printing, or FDM with a 0.2mm nozzle.

name: Derelict Station Terrain Set
description:
This is a 40 piece derelict station terrain set. 

Unlike most of our catalogue, this set is designed for FDM printing, utalizing the "spiralize outer contour" or "vase mode" function.

name: Archvillain Adventures - Tome of Demons Vol. V
description:
⚔️ Looking for 5e adventures? Click HERE!

"The sky grows darker with each passing hour, aboard the floating resort of Heaven’s Envy. Demons slip through the storms while nobles turn on one another. Will you expose the corruption before the final storm breaks?"

This is an adventure compatible with the 5th edition of Dungeons & Dragons! These adventures include a pdf document for you to run with your party as well as printable map/s and exclusive creature stat blocks!

This module is a Fifth Edition adventure for four to six adventurers with an average party level (APL) of 8.Due to the nature of this adventure, parties that include characters with a fly speed and characters that are resistant to lightning damage will have an advantage. It takes place in the Drifting Heavens but can be incorporated into any campaign setting, and it can be played as a stand-alone module or as a quest in an ongoing campaign. If you wish to include our miniatures in your game, find the bundle here:

https://www.myminifactory.com/object/3d-print-tome-of-demons-vol-v-bundle-736708

Adventure Synopsis:

-The characters arrive in Heaven's Envy, investigate Enzel’s death and face the cultists hiding within the retreat.

-As the new wave of storms manifests, the party must deal with the summoned demons as well as the discord sown by Pazuzu’s demonic influence.

-Before the thirteenth storm breaks out, the characters must convince Glenda to remain pure of heart and not fall from grace.

-During the final storm, they fight Marion in his demonic form and decide whether to cut a deal with Pazuzu himself.
